ration."],[496,"Operating runs: start/preflight workflows, run drafts, reruns, promotion, cancel, resolve approvals."],[1129,"Operation"],[708,"Operations are organized into eight groups, exposed as OpenAPI tags:\n**workflows**, **runs**, **approvals**, **automation** (schedules + workflow\nendpoints), **library** (agents, skills, knowledge, hooks), **distribution**\n(bundles, packages), **admin** (tokens, secrets, audit, alerts, updates), and\n**system** (health, version, menu, dashboard, runners)."],[918,"Option"],[895,"Optional default chat/thread for non-approval notifications."],[1012,"Optional pre-seeded bootstrap admin/runner token (containers); on host installs one is generated into the data dir"],[943,"Options: `--units <units>` (systemd units to restart, default\n`runyard runyard-runner`) and `--grace-ms <ms>` (bounded drain window before\naborting — in-flight runs are never killed)."],[469,"Other consumers reference secrets **by name only**: hook profiles declare `secretNames`, and their readiness checks report missing *names*, never values."],[761,"Other resources (see `/openapi.json` for the rest — schedules, catalog\nagents/skills/knowledge, hooks, workflow bundles and packages, workflow\nendpoints, runners, dashboard):"],[223,"Outcome"],[1292,"Over MCP the same payload goes to `create_workflow` as the `workflow` argument. The response definition carries `workflow.bundleId` instead of the inline source — the bytes now live in the Hub DB. Runners fetch the bundle at execution time; nothing needs to exist on any runner's filesystem beforehand."],[291,"Path"],[468,"Payload fields with credential-like names are redacted in approval cards and other presentation surfaces."],[93,"Per-kind consequences"],[268,"Per-run model-call usage as a first-class streamed signal, hard spend budgets, and the metering gateway at the inference boundary."],[931,"Pin the run to a specific workflow git SHA (requires workflow versioning)"],[255,"Platform"],[964,"pnpm"],[1036,"Po